(136, 'wp_installer_settings', 'a:4:{s:17:"_pre_1_0_clean_up";b:1;s:12:"repositories";a:1:{s:4:"wpml";a:1:{s:4:"data";a:11:{s:2:"id";s:38:"wpml-the-wordpress-multilingual-plugin";s:4:"name";s:40:"WPML - The WordPress Multilingual Plugin";s:12:"product-name";s:4:"WPML";s:3:"url";s:16:"https://wpml.org";s:24:"site_keys_management_url";s:31:"https://wpml.org/account/sites/";s:12:"support_tags";a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:4:"name";s:4:"WPML";s:3:"url";s:39:"https://wpml.org/forums/topic-tag/wpml/";}}s:8:"packages";a:2:{i:451018;a:7:{s:2:"id";s:16:"multilingual-cms";s:4:"name";s:16:"Multilingual CMS";s:11:"description";s:102:"The complete package, good for any multilingual site, including also multilingual WooCommerce support.";s:9:"image_url";s:61:"https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/wpml-logo1-01.png";s:5:"order";i:0;s:6:"parent";i:0;s:8:"products";a:2:{s:25:"multilingual-cms-for-life";a:10:{s:4:"name";s:25:"Multilingual CMS for life";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:5:"price";s:3:"195";s:17:"subscription_type";i:6721;s:22:"subscription_type_text";s:25:"Multilingual CMS for life";s:17:"subscription_info";s:27:"Subscription with no expiry";s:3:"url";s:50:"https://wpml.org/?add-to-cart=162039&amp;buy_now=1";s:8:"renewals";a:0:{}s:8:"upgrades";a:0:{}s:9:"downloads";a:9:{i:0;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:21:"WPML Multilingual CMS";s:4:"slug";s:26:"sitepress-multilingual-cms";s:11:"description";s:782:"WPML combines multilingual content authoring with powerful translation management. It powers corporate sites and is simple enough for bloggers.\r\n\r\n<dl><dt>Turns WordPress multilingual</dt><dd>Every element in WordPress becomes multilingual. This include pages, posts, tags, categories, custom types and even comments.</dd><dt>Virtual language directories and languages in different domains</dt><dd>You can display translations in URLs such as <em>example.com/es/</em>, <em>example.com/fr/</em> or in completely different domains, or sub-domains, per language.</dd><dt>Convenient translation controls</dt><dd>When you view the lists of pages and posts, you''ll see what''s already translated and what not. You can add translations from the list-view or while editing content.</dd></dl>";s:9:"changelog";s:8726:"<h4>3.1.9.7</h4>Fixed a problem with menu translation<h4>3.1.9.6</h4>* Security fixes<h4>3.1.9.5</h4>* "Illegal mix of collation" error\r\n* Categories by languages are not displayed<h4>3.1.9.4</h4>Added support for WordPress 4.2.<h4>3.1.9.3</h4>Additional fixes to URLs with non-English characters.<h4>3.1.9.2</h4>Fixed issue with saving posts that have slugs in different languages.<h4>3.1.9.1</h4>Fixed URL resolution for non-English URLs.<h4>3.1.9</h4>Security update<h4>3.1.8.6</h4>Small improvement to mechanism for remote config files.<h4>3.1.8.5</h4>Small improvement to Installer, which will help get WPML updates.<h4>3.1.8.4</h4>Fixed several incompatibilities with WooCommerce, menu translation and taxonomy translation.<h4>3.1.8.3</h4>Stability update - fixes issues with the taxonomy translation admin screen in WPML and WooCommerce multilingual.<h4>3.1.8.2</h4>Updated to fix issue with taxonomy translation page and duplicate media items.<h4>3.1.8.1</h4>Quick fix for WooCommerce updates.<h4>3.1.8</h4>Major updates to taxonomy translation and general stability improvements.<h4>3.1.7.2</h4>* Removed mistakenly added anonymous function, causing issues with versions of PHP <5.3\r\n* Fixed for wrong usage of static method\r\n<h4>3.1.7.1</h4>Fixed glitch with translation management<h4>3.1.7</h4>Moved Installer back to WPML and a number of other improvements.<h4>3.1.6</h4>Bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>3.1.5</h4>Full compatibility for WordPress 3.9 and updates for PHP 5.5.<h4>3.1.4</h4>Major performance and stability updates.<h4>3.0.2-a</h4>Fixes a bug which caused translations to be disconnected in some situations.<h4>3.0.1</h4>Tiny bugfix version for "cannot delete" message and other small glitches<h4>3.0</h4>New GUI, better menu sync and big improvements for multilingual e-commerce.<h4>2.9.3</h4>A great number of improvements and fixes and WooCommerce Multilingual.<h4>2.9.2</h4>Removes deprecation warnings on WordPress 3.6.\r\nImproves performance when scanning many new strings.<h4>2.9.1</h4>This is a bugfix release, addressing some issues that came up in WPML 2.9:\r\n\r\n* Slug translation issues\r\n* Content appearing twice with some themes\r\n* Content disappeared from the WordPress admin\r\n* WPML didn‚Äôt mark duplicate content as duplicate\r\n<h4>2.9</h4><h3>Features</h3>\r\nTitle tags added to navigation\r\nrel=canonical now optional configurable under WPML -&gt; Languages ‚Üí SEO Options\r\nAllow to select all languages when sending documents to translation from the Translation Dashboard\r\nImproved Import/export .po from String Translation screen\r\nFlag only language switcher. Including horizontal layout.\r\nPreserve url parameters in the language switcher\r\nUse directory for default language\r\nDuplicate all custom fields and taxonomy when duplicating the post\r\nNew function in the Troubleshooting section to set update translation tables after changing the slug for custom posts or custom taxonomies that had translated elements.\r\nAllow re-assigning translation jobs\r\nSupport wildcards in wpml-config.xml for entries in the options table\r\nAdded the Malay language\r\n<h3>Bugs</h3>\r\nBrowser language redirect (some IE versions)\r\nCustom flag icons do not display on post table columns (posts screen)\r\nSlug translation in LS not working when WPML default language is different than ST original language\r\nLanguage order not applied before first drag\r\nChanging the slug of a taxonomy breaks things\r\nWrong url for custom posts with translated slug.\r\nWPML making Bbpress menu disappear\r\nNotifications not being sent to translators when jobs were cancelled\r\n<h3>Misc</h3>\r\nChanged references to deprecated jQuery function live() -&gt; WPML minimum required WordPress version is now 3.3\r\nWPML Core ‚Äì 2.9\r\nWPML String Translation ‚Äì 1.8\r\nWPML Translation Management ‚Äì 1.7\r\nWPML Media ‚Äì 1.5<h4>2.8.2</h4>Compatible with WordPress 3.6.<h4>2.8.1</h4>Renamed the mobile detection function name to avoid conflicts with other plugins.<h4>2.8</h4>1. Support Different Domains for Languages in WordPress Multisite\r\n2. Mobile-Friendly Language Switcher\r\n3. Allow logging in from on different domains\r\n4. Drag-and-Drop Ordering for Languages<h4>2.7.1</h4>Fixes a few PHP warnings that came up with 2.7 release.<h4>2.7</h4>Improves menu sync functionality and adds a significant performance boost together with the updated String Translation.<h4>2.6.4.1</h4>Added support for Disqus comments, some more fixes of WordPress 3.5 glitches and several small bugs.<h4>2.6.3</h4>Bugfix version that resolves a number of issues related with WordPress 3.5 and some themes and other plugins.<h4>2.6.2</h4><ul>\r\n	<li>Complete support for WordPress 3.5</li>\r\n	<li>Added support for slug translation for custom post types (experimental)</li>\r\n	<li>Fixed a great number of issues with WooCommerce Multilingual</li>\r\n	<li>Moved WPML admin language switcher to WordPress bar</li>\r\n	<li>And a number of bug fixes and overall improvements</li>\r\n</ul><h4>2.6.1</h4>Stability and performance updates. Main bugs fixed include translation for custom fields with serialized arrays and menu synchronization.<h4>2.6.0</h4><ul>\r\n	<li>Added automatic downloading for WordPress translation core</li>\r\n	<li>Improved support for W3TC</li>\r\n	<li>Added fixes for WooCommerce</li>\r\n	<li>Separated the install process to the new Installer plugin</li>\r\n	<li>A bunch of bug fixes and performance improvements</li>\r\n</ul><h4>2.5.2</h4>Fixes several bugs for WordPress multiuser and ICanLocalize interface in WordPress 3.4.<h4>2.5.1</h4>Added support for Google language reference and to convert non ASCII chars in URLs.\r\n\r\nAlso, a good number of fixes and improvements all around.<h4>2.4.3</h4>Stability release with a host of fixes and improvements to existing features.<h4>2.4.2</h4>Adds content duplication logic, which allows displaying untranslated content in different languages.<h4>2.4.1</h4>Allows duplicate post names in different languages.<h4>2.4.0</h4>Added:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Menu Synchronization</strong>¬†- no more need to manually build menus in different languages, WPML can build them for you</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Filter by Parent in the Translation Dashboard</strong>¬†- easily select groups of child pages, or posts by category for translations</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Language Switcher in Menu</strong>¬†- add WPML''s language switcher to WordPress menus</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Author Names Translation Optional</strong>¬†- choose which profiles to translate via the String Translation screen</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Translation for the ‚ÄòUncategorized‚Äô Category</strong>¬†- the default category can have a meaningful name in different languages</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Full Support for Types and Views</strong>¬†- WPML and our new custom data plugin work perfectly together</li>\r\n</ul><h4>2.3.4</h4>Includes complete compatibility with WP E-Commerce (requires the free glue plugin <em>WP E-Commerce Multilingual</em>).<h4>2.3.3</h4>Bugfix release, handling all sorts of issues related with categories, tags and taxonomy.\r\n\r\nAlso, fully tested with WordPress 3.2.<h4>2.3.2</h4>This release improves usability and fixes some potentially confusing parts of WPML.\r\n<h3>What''s new</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Real-time Custom Fields Sync</li>\r\n	<li>Real-time Category and Taxonomy Update</li>\r\n	<li>Translation for Author Fields</li>\r\n	<li>Smarter Admin Language Switcher</li>\r\n	<li>Simplified Theme Localization Options</li>\r\n	<li>Full Support for All GetText Calls</li>\r\n	<li>Synchronization for Publish Date</li>\r\n	<li>Easy to Resign Translators</li>\r\n</ul><h4>2.3.0</h4>Major release with major new functionality:\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Admin bar content-language switcher</li>\r\n<li>Auto-register strings for translation</li>\r\n<li>Sending Strings for translation by your assigned translators</li>\r\n<li>Multilingual-Text Widget</li>\r\n<li>Improvements and fixes to the Translation Editor</li>\r\n<li>Tested with WordPress 3.2</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>2.2.2.1</h4>Fixed a few bugs that were recently introduced:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fatal error for WordPress 3.0 in Multisite mode</li>\r\n<li>Locale value set incorrectly, in conjunction with plugins that load prematurely</li>\r\n<li>WordPress core always trying to upgrade to the default language</li>\r\n<li>Author page URLs incorrect</li>\r\n<li>Pages that begin with language names fail</li>\r\n<li>Negative category names (exclude) not working on translated pages</li>\r\n<li>Endless loop related with categories</li>\r\n<li>PHP notices in some situations</li>\r\n</ul><h4>2.2.2</h4><ul><li>Serious bug fixed, which may lead to loss of language information</li>\r\n<li>Added support for network activation</li>\r\n<li>Improved compatibility with complex themes</li>\r\n<li>Performance improvements and memory reduction in the Admin pages</li>\r\n</ul>";s:7:"version";s:7:"3.1.9.7";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-05-06 08:19:50";s:3:"url";s:47:"https://wpml.org/?download=6088&version=3.1.9.7";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:26:"sitepress-multilingual-cms";}i:1;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:23:"WPML String Translation";s:4:"slug";s:23:"wpml-string-translation";s:11:"description";s:754:"<strong>Allows translating texts in the theme, in other plugins and in the WordPress Admin.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: red;">This is an add-on plugin. It requires the base <em>"WPML Multilingual CMS"</em> to run.</span>\r\n\r\nThe String Translation package includes support for static and dynamic texts.\r\n\r\nStatic texts are hard-coded into the PHP source. Normally, they are translated using .mo files, but with the String Translation package, they can be translated right from within the WordPress Admin.\r\n\r\nDynamic texts is everything that is user-editable. The site''s tagline is an example. Other dynamic texts are often found in the theme settings (like site footer) and in plugins. SEO plugins include many dynamic texts, for titles and meta-data.";s:9:"changelog";s:2996:"<h4>2.1.4</h4>Security tightening.<h4>2.1.3</h4>Fixed a bug related to translating custom post types.<h4>2.1.2</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.9.4 on WordPress 4.2.<h4>2.1.1</h4>Additional fixes to URLs with non-English characters.<h4>2.1</h4>Security update<h4>2.0.14</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.4.<h4>2.0.13</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.3<h4>2.0.12</h4>Updated to fix string registration filter for theme developers.<h4>2.0.11</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.2.<h4>2.0.10</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.<h4>2.0.9.1</h4>Fixed a problem with XML config files, causing PHP errors and untranslated strings.<h4>2.0.9</h4>The fixed dependency bug in 2.0.8 didn''t cover the case of String Translation being activate by users before the WPML core plugin. This was still causing an issue, making the plugin not visible in the menu (and actually not enabled). This should be now fixed.<h4>2.0.8</h4>Fixed dependency issue with WPML core when not active, or during upgrades<h4>2.0.7</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.7.<h4>2.0.6</h4>Update for WPML 3.1.6 with bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>2.0.5</h4>Updates for WordPress 3.9 and PHP 5.5.<h4>2.0.4</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.4.<h4>2.0.1</h4>Small bugfix version for WPML 3.0.1<h4>2.0</h4>WordPress with WPML 3.0.<h4>1.9</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.3.<h4>1.8.2</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.2.<h4>1.8.1</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.1.<h4>1.8</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.<h4>1.7.1</h4>Works with WPML 2.8.2 and WordPress up to 3.6.<h4>1.7</h4>Works with WPML 2.8.<h4>1.6.1</h4>Fixes a bug with translations not showing in version 1.6.<h4>1.6</h4>Up to x2 improvement in site performance.<h4>1.5.4</h4>Bugfix update.<h4>1.5.3</h4>Fixes a number of issues related to WordPress 3.5.<h4>1.5.2</h4>Added support for localizing CPT slugs.<h4>1.5.1</h4>Bugfix release.<h4>1.5.0</h4>Performance improvements and bug fixes.<h4>1.4.0</h4>Major improvements to caching for better performance in public pages and admin pages.<h4>1.3.0</h4>Stability release.<h4>1.2.9</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.2 and includes a number of bug fixes.<h4>1.2.8</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.1.<h4>1.2.7</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.0 and includes a number of new features and improvements.<h4>1.2.6</h4>Includes several bug fixes and translations to new languages.<h4>1.2.5</h4>Fixes issues related with taxonomy. Works with WPML 2.3.3.<h4>1.2.4</h4>Improves usability and fixes some small bugs.<h4>1.2.3</h4>New features:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Added an option to auto-register strings</li>\r\n<li>Admins can send strings to translation using the Translation Management module</li>\r\n</ul><h4>1.2.2.1</h4>Fixes a few errors that were introduced in recent versions.<h4>1.2.2</h4>General performance improvements and bug fixes.<h4>1.2.1</h4>Bugfix release. Brings back the Admin Strings selection with fully working functionality.<h4>1.2.0</h4>Switches direction when editing Right-to-Left strings.<h4>1.1.1</h4>Full support for WordPress 3.1.<h4>1.1.0</h4>Fixes a number of bugs related with custom types.<h4>1.0.0</h4>First release of the commercial version.";s:7:"version";s:5:"2.1.4";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-05-21 13:38:43";s:3:"url";s:45:"https://wpml.org/?download=6092&version=2.1.4";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:23:"wpml-string-translation";}i:2;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:27:"WPML Translation Management";s:4:"slug";s:27:"wpml-translation-management";s:11:"description";s:1260:"<strong>The Translation Management package helps run translations for large WordPress sites.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: red;">This is an add-on plugin. It requires the base <em>"WPML Multilingual CMS"</em> to run.</span>\r\n\r\n<dl><dt>Translator Role</dt><dd>Site admins can turn ordinary WordPress users into translators. Translators can only edit specific content that was assigned to them for translation.</dd><dt>Centralized translation control</dt><dd>Admins get a complete overview of what''s already translated and what needs translation or update. They can send content to translation to specific translators and track progress.</dd><dt>Translation queues</dt><dd>Each translator has a queue of pending jobs. Translators don''t need to look for what to do, it just waits for them.</dd><dt>Side-by-Side translation editor</dt><dd>When translating, you see both the original and translation and what changed. You can conveniently move from one field to the other, and switch between Visual and HTML views.</dd><dt>Automatic link translation</dt><dd>Translators don''t need to worry about interlinked content. WPML will automatically update links to point to other translated content. Translators only need to translate the text and nothing else.</dd></dl>";s:9:"changelog";s:2468:"<h4>1.9.11</h4>Additional fixes to URLs with non-English characters<h4>1.9.10</h4>Security update<h4>1.9.9</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.4<h4>1.9.8</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.3.<h4>1.9.7</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.<h4>1.9.6</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.7.<h4>1.9.5</h4>Update for WPML 3.1.6 with bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>1.9.4</h4>Updates for WordPress 3.9 and PHP 5.5.<h4>1.9.3</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.4.<h4>1.9.1</h4>Small bugfix version for WPML 3.0.1<h4>1.9</h4>Works with WPML 3.0.<h4>1.8</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.3.<h4>1.7.2</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.2.<h4>1.7.1</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.1.<h4>1.7</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.<h4>1.6.1</h4>Works with WPML 2.8.2 and WordPress 3.6.<h4>1.6</h4>Works with WPML 2.8<h4>1.5</h4>New option for selecting documents.<h4>1.4.4</h4>Added checks to prevent errors with documents that have illegal character names.<h4>1.4.3</h4>Fixes a number of issues related with WordPress 3.5.<h4>1.4.2</h4>Added a new display filter for content that needs updating (but it not new)<h4>1.4.1</h4>Bugfix release.<h4>1.4.0</h4>Changed cost estimate for ICanLocalize translation and fixed a number of warnings and notices.<h4>1.3.1</h4>Fixes some bugs with ICanLocalize interface. Works with WPML 2.5.2.<h4>1.3.0</h4>Improvements for translation of custom fields, with complete support for repeating fields.<h4>1.2.9</h4>Stability release.<h4>1.2.8</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.2 and includes the content duplication logic.<h4>1.2.7</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.1.<h4>1.2.6</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.0 and includes a number of new features and improvements. The filter section in the Translation Dashboard has been enhanced for better usability and allows selecting items by parent.<h4>1.2.5</h4>Updated to support new functionality for WP E-Commerce and several bug fixes.<h4>1.2.4</h4>Improves usability and fixes several small bugs.<h4>1.2.3</h4>Allows translating strings using the assigned translators.<h4>1.2.2</h4>Added automatic link updates for translated pages.<h4>1.2.1</h4>Bugfix release.<h4>1.2.0</h4><ul>\r\n<li>Added Right-to-Left support.</li>\r\n<li>Displays the existing translation when sending documents for update.</li>\r\n<li>Shows the difference between previous originals to current originals when updating translations.</li>\r\n</ul><h4>1.1.1</h4>Added full support for WordPress 3.1.<h4>1.1.0</h4>Fixed a bug:\r\n\r\n"Jobs can remain in stuck state if sending to incorrect translators"<h4>1.0.0</h4>First release of the commercial version.";s:7:"version";s:6:"1.9.11";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-03-12 16:09:05";s:3:"url";s:46:"https://wpml.org/?download=6094&version=1.9.11";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:27:"wpml-translation-management";}i:3;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:17:"WPML Sticky Links";s:4:"slug";s:17:"wpml-sticky-links";s:11:"description";s:894:"<strong>Turns all internal links into unbreakable, by following the document that''s being linked to.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: red;">This is an add-on plugin. It requires the base <em>"WPML Multilingual CMS"</em> to run.</span>\r\n\r\nPages, posts, categories, tags and custom types all have default URLs. These URLs point to the object ID. No matter what changes the pages undergo, the IDs always remain the same, identifying them in the CMS.\r\n\r\nThis plugin converts all links in the DB to the default URLs. Then, just as the pages are displayed, it replaces the links back to the permalinks.\r\n\r\nWhen you view the DB, you''ll see ''ugly'' looking links. However, when visitors view your site, they would always see the up-to-date links.\r\n\r\nYou can change slugs, hierarchy and permalink structure and all links always remain valid.\r\n\r\nSee the <a href="/?page_id=594">Sticky Links user guide</a>.";s:9:"changelog";s:1318:"<h4>1.3.9</h4>Additional fixes to URLs with non-English characters<h4>1.3.8</h4>Security update<h4>1.3.7</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.4<h4>1.3.6</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.<h4>1.3.5</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.7.<h4>1.3.4</h4>Update for WPML 3.1.6 with bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>1.3.3</h4>Updates for WordPress 3.9 and PHP 5.5.<h4>1.3.2</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.4.<h4>1.3</h4>Updated translations.<h4>1.2.1</h4>Bugfix release<h4>1.2.0</h4>Fixed a number of bugs related to reverting Sticky Links in different URL formats. Also improved Sticky Link detection in content.<h4>1.1.8</h4>Stability release<h4>1.1.7</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.0 and includes a number of new features and improvements.<h4>1.1.6</h4>Includes several bug fixes and translations to new languages.<h4>1.1.5</h4>Fixes issues related with taxonomy translation. Works with WPML 2.3.3.<h4>1.1.4</h4>Fixes a number of issues and improves Sticky Links for taxonomies. Works with WPML 2.3.1.<h4>1.1.3</h4>Improved performance and small bug fixes.<h4>1.1.2</h4>Improved support for multiple pages with the same name.<h4>1.1.1</h4>Bugfix release.<h4>1.1.0</h4>Fixed Sticky Links functionality for links that include classes and other attributes.<h4>1.0.1</h4>Added full support for WordPress 3.1.<h4>1.0.0</h4>First release of the commercial version.";s:7:"version";s:5:"1.3.9";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-03-12 16:09:43";s:3:"url";s:45:"https://wpml.org/?download=6090&version=1.3.9";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:17:"wpml-sticky-links";}i:4;a:11:{s:4:"name";s:26:"WPML Translation Analytics";s:4:"slug";s:26:"wpml-translation-analytics";s:11:"description";s:588:"<p><strong>Helps site admins manage and track the status of translation work.</strong></p>\r\n<p>When you''re working with a team of translators, often located in different parts of the world and working different hours, staying on top of translation progress can be complicated.</p>\r\n<p>This plugin will let you manage your site''s translation easily and efficiently. You''ll immediately see the current status of translation, progress over time, and how you''re doing compared to project deadlines.</p>\r\n<p>This plugin requires the base WPML and Translation Management, in order to run.</p>\r\n";s:9:"changelog";s:318:"<h4>1.0.7</h4>Security update<h4>1.0.6</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.7<h4>1.0.5</h4>Update for WPML 3.1.6 with bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>1.0.4</h4>Updates for WordPress 3.9 and PHP 5.5.<h4>1.0.3</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.4.<h4>1.0.1</h4>Complete translation to several languages.<h4>1.0.0</h4>Initial release.";s:7:"version";s:5:"1.0.7";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-03-10 10:13:31";s:3:"url";s:46:"https://wpml.org/?download=78197&version=1.0.7";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:26:"wpml-translation-analytics";s:15:"version-for-icl";s:5:"1.0.6";s:11:"url-for-icl";s:46:"https://wpml.org/?download=78197&version=1.0.6";}i:5;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:12:"WPML CMS Nav";s:4:"slug";s:12:"wpml-cms-nav";s:11:"description";s:589:"<strong>Creates navigation elements, which you can use with any theme.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: red;">This is an add-on plugin. It requires the base <em>"WPML Multilingual CMS"</em> to run.</span>\r\n\r\n<dl><dt>Breadcrumb trail</dt><dd>Shows a trail back to the home page.</dd><dt>Sidebar navigation</dt><dd>A widget that you can add to the sidebar. It shows the current page next to neighboring pages.</dd><dt>Drop-down menu</dt><dd>Shows the site''s top-level pages and their child pages. The drop-down menu supports item-hooks, which allow customizing the content of cells.</dd></dl>";s:9:"changelog";s:1050:"<h4>1.4.7</h4>Security update<h4>1.4.6</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.4.<h4>1.4.5</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.7.<h4>1.4.4</h4>Update for WPML 3.1.6 with bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>1.4.3</h4>Updates for WordPress 3.9 and PHP 5.5.<h4>1.4.2</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.4.<h4>1.4</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.3.<h4>1.3</h4>Translations update.<h4>1.2.7</h4>Fixed several minor security notices.<h4>1.2.6</h4>Stability release<h4>1.2.5</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.0 and includes a number of new features and improvements.<h4>1.2.4</h4>Includes small bug fixes and new translation files.<h4>1.2.3</h4>Mainly bug fixes and support for new functionality in WPML 2.3.0.<h4>1.2.2</h4>Fixed bugs related with navigation caching, to improve performance and reduce DB size.<h4>1.2.1</h4>Bugfix release.<h4>1.2.0</h4>Added full support for Custom Post Archives in the breadcrumbs trail.<h4>1.1.1</h4>Added full support for WordPress 3.1.<h4>1.1.0</h4>Fixes a number of bugs, related with navigation for custom types.<h4>1.0.0</h4>First release of the commercial version.";s:7:"version";s:5:"1.4.7";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-03-10 10:13:50";s:3:"url";s:45:"https://wpml.org/?download=6096&version=1.4.7";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:12:"wpml-cms-nav";}i:6;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:10:"WPML Media";s:4:"slug";s:10:"wpml-media";s:11:"description";s:603:"Manages translations for WordPress Media. This plugin will allow to use the same uploaded media (images, audio, movies, etc.) in different translations, without having to re-upload duplicate content.\r\n\r\nWhen you insert media to posts and pages, Media Translation will offer to auto-duplicate it to translations. Then, when you use the WordPress <em>gallery</em> shorttag, the same images will appear in all translations.\r\n\r\nMedia Translation also auto-sets featured images for translation.\r\n\r\nIt works in different translation modes. You can create translations manually or using the Translation Editor.";s:9:"changelog";s:1482:"<h4>2.1.9</h4>Security update<h4>2.1.8</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.4.<h4>2.1.7</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.<h4>2.1.6</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.7.<h4>2.1.5</h4>Update for WPML 3.1.6 with bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>2.1.4</h4>Updates for WordPress 3.9 and PHP 5.5.<h4>2.1.3</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.4.<h4>2.1.1</h4>Small bugfix version for WPML 3.0.1<h4>2.1</h4>Improvements for WooCommerce Multilingual 3.0.<h4>2.0.2</h4>Uses the same language mapping as all other WPML components use. Fully supports WooCommerce.<h4>1.6</h4>New GUI that makes the functionality of the Media Translation a lot clearer.\r\nFixed a number of issues with media items not getting languages and disappearing from the WordPress admin.\r\nImproved synchronization for featured images in different languages.<h4>1.5</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.<h4>1.4</h4>Bug fixes.<h4>1.3</h4>Stability improvements.<h4>1.2.3</h4>Fixed a bug with WordPress prepare statement for 3.5.<h4>1.2.2</h4>Fixes a number of issues with WordPress 3.5.<h4>1.2.1</h4>Bugfix release.<h4>1.2.0</h4>Major performance improvements.<h4>1.1.0</h4>Fixes a bug that caused attachments uploaded via the Media management screen to not have language information.<h4>1.0.1</h4>Small bug fixes and added translations.<h4>1.0.0</h4>First release. Look for the new controls in the language boxes when editing posts. There''s also a new menu, <em>WPML-&gt;Media translation</em>, that allows to auto-generate duplicate Attachments for existing content.";s:7:"version";s:5:"2.1.9";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-03-10 10:14:10";s:3:"url";s:45:"https://wpml.org/?download=7474&version=2.1.9";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:10:"wpml-media";}i:7;a:11:{s:4:"name";s:10:"WPML XLIFF";s:4:"slug";s:10:"wpml-xliff";s:11:"description";s:692:"<strong>The XLIFF package allows exporting translation jobs to desktop translation software.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: red;">This is an add-on plugin. It requires the base <em>"WPML Multilingual CMS"</em> to run.</span>\r\n\r\nThis package creates XLIFF files and includes them in the translation job notification emails. Translators will be able to use their favorite CAT tools to translate offline and return the translations to WPML.\r\n\r\nIn order to use it, you must install WPML Translation Management. The XLIFF interface is added to the translation jobs list and notification emails.\r\n\r\nYou can read about how it works in the <a href="/?page_id=8012">XLIFF interface documentation</a>.";s:9:"changelog";s:471:"<h4>0.9.8</h4>Security update<h4>0.9.7</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.<h4>0.9.6</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.7.<h4>0.9.5</h4>Update for WPML 3.1.6 with bug fixes and performance improvements. Allows to choose the XLIFF version when generating files.<h4>0.9.4</h4>Updates for WordPress 3.9 and PHP 5.5.<h4>0.9.3</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.4.<h4>0.9.1</h4>Stability release<h4>0.9.0</h4>First release. This release is tested with a number of CAT tools including Trados, MemQ and others.";s:7:"version";s:5:"0.9.8";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-03-10 10:14:34";s:3:"url";s:45:"https://wpml.org/?download=8066&version=0.9.8";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:10:"wpml-xliff";s:15:"version-for-icl";s:5:"0.9.7";s:11:"url-for-icl";s:45:"https://wpml.org/?download=8066&version=0.9.7";}i:8;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:26:"Gravity Forms Multilingual";s:4:"slug";s:25:"gravityforms-multilingual";s:11:"description";s:333:"Allows to use WPML with Gravity Forms, to create multilingual contact forms.\r\n\r\nTo use this plugin, you''ll need WPML''s <strong>String Translation</strong> and <strong>Translation Management</strong> modules. Once installed, go to the <strong>Translation Dashboard</strong>. There, you''ll see the contact forms, ready for translation.";s:9:"changelog";s:455:"<h4>1.2.2</h4>Added support for Gravity Forms 1.9.x.\r\nSecurity fixes.<h4>1.2.1</h4>Added support for more GravityForms fields for features.<h4>1.2</h4>Added support for more GravityForms features.<h4>1.1</h4>Added support for new Gravity Forms texts and validation messages.<h4>0.9.3</h4>Fixed the language of the ''thank you'' page.<h4>0.9.2</h4>Fixes a number of issues with special characters in form fields.<h4>0.9.1</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.1 and above.";s:7:"version";s:5:"1.2.2";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-03-12 16:21:47";s:3:"url";s:45:"https://wpml.org/?download=8882&version=1.2.2";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:25:"gravityforms-multilingual";}}}s:16:"multilingual-cms";a:10:{s:4:"name";s:16:"Multilingual CMS";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:5:"price";s:2:"79";s:17:"subscription_type";i:6719;s:22:"subscription_type_text";s:16:"Multilingual CMS";s:17:"subscription_info";s:19:"Yearly subscription";s:3:"url";s:50:"https://wpml.org/?add-to-cart=162035&amp;buy_now=1";s:8:"renewals";a:1:{s:24:"multilingual-cms-renewal";a:5:{s:4:"name";s:24:"Multilingual CMS renewal";s:11:"call2action";s:0:"";s:11:"description";s:96:"Extend your Multilingual CMS account by another year, providing continuous support and upgrades.";s:5:"price";s:2:"39";s:3:"url";s:50:"https://wpml.org/?add-to-cart=162037&amp;buy_now=1";}}s:8:"upgrades";a:1:{s:42:"multilingual-cms-for-life-upgrade-from-cms";a:7:{s:4:"name";s:42:"Multilingual CMS for life upgrade from CMS";s:11:"call2action";s:0:"";s:11:"description";s:113:"Save money and hassle by upgrading to a lifetime account. You will receive upgrades and support for WPML forever.";s:5:"price";s:3:"116";s:17:"subscription_type";i:6721;s:3:"url";s:50:"https://wpml.org/?add-to-cart=162041&amp;buy_now=1";s:17:"including_expired";i:1;}}s:9:"downloads";a:9:{i:0;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:21:"WPML Multilingual CMS";s:4:"slug";s:26:"sitepress-multilingual-cms";s:11:"description";s:782:"WPML combines multilingual content authoring with powerful translation management. It powers corporate sites and is simple enough for bloggers.\r\n\r\n<dl><dt>Turns WordPress multilingual</dt><dd>Every element in WordPress becomes multilingual. This include pages, posts, tags, categories, custom types and even comments.</dd><dt>Virtual language directories and languages in different domains</dt><dd>You can display translations in URLs such as <em>example.com/es/</em>, <em>example.com/fr/</em> or in completely different domains, or sub-domains, per language.</dd><dt>Convenient translation controls</dt><dd>When you view the lists of pages and posts, you''ll see what''s already translated and what not. You can add translations from the list-view or while editing content.</dd></dl>";s:9:"changelog";s:8726:"<h4>3.1.9.7</h4>Fixed a problem with menu translation<h4>3.1.9.6</h4>* Security fixes<h4>3.1.9.5</h4>* "Illegal mix of collation" error\r\n* Categories by languages are not displayed<h4>3.1.9.4</h4>Added support for WordPress 4.2.<h4>3.1.9.3</h4>Additional fixes to URLs with non-English characters.<h4>3.1.9.2</h4>Fixed issue with saving posts that have slugs in different languages.<h4>3.1.9.1</h4>Fixed URL resolution for non-English URLs.<h4>3.1.9</h4>Security update<h4>3.1.8.6</h4>Small improvement to mechanism for remote config files.<h4>3.1.8.5</h4>Small improvement to Installer, which will help get WPML updates.<h4>3.1.8.4</h4>Fixed several incompatibilities with WooCommerce, menu translation and taxonomy translation.<h4>3.1.8.3</h4>Stability update - fixes issues with the taxonomy translation admin screen in WPML and WooCommerce multilingual.<h4>3.1.8.2</h4>Updated to fix issue with taxonomy translation page and duplicate media items.<h4>3.1.8.1</h4>Quick fix for WooCommerce updates.<h4>3.1.8</h4>Major updates to taxonomy translation and general stability improvements.<h4>3.1.7.2</h4>* Removed mistakenly added anonymous function, causing issues with versions of PHP <5.3\r\n* Fixed for wrong usage of static method\r\n<h4>3.1.7.1</h4>Fixed glitch with translation management<h4>3.1.7</h4>Moved Installer back to WPML and a number of other improvements.<h4>3.1.6</h4>Bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>3.1.5</h4>Full compatibility for WordPress 3.9 and updates for PHP 5.5.<h4>3.1.4</h4>Major performance and stability updates.<h4>3.0.2-a</h4>Fixes a bug which caused translations to be disconnected in some situations.<h4>3.0.1</h4>Tiny bugfix version for "cannot delete" message and other small glitches<h4>3.0</h4>New GUI, better menu sync and big improvements for multilingual e-commerce.<h4>2.9.3</h4>A great number of improvements and fixes and WooCommerce Multilingual.<h4>2.9.2</h4>Removes deprecation warnings on WordPress 3.6.\r\nImproves performance when scanning many new strings.<h4>2.9.1</h4>This is a bugfix release, addressing some issues that came up in WPML 2.9:\r\n\r\n* Slug translation issues\r\n* Content appearing twice with some themes\r\n* Content disappeared from the WordPress admin\r\n* WPML didn‚Äôt mark duplicate content as duplicate\r\n<h4>2.9</h4><h3>Features</h3>\r\nTitle tags added to navigation\r\nrel=canonical now optional configurable under WPML -&gt; Languages ‚Üí SEO Options\r\nAllow to select all languages when sending documents to translation from the Translation Dashboard\r\nImproved Import/export .po from String Translation screen\r\nFlag only language switcher. Including horizontal layout.\r\nPreserve url parameters in the language switcher\r\nUse directory for default language\r\nDuplicate all custom fields and taxonomy when duplicating the post\r\nNew function in the Troubleshooting section to set update translation tables after changing the slug for custom posts or custom taxonomies that had translated elements.\r\nAllow re-assigning translation jobs\r\nSupport wildcards in wpml-config.xml for entries in the options table\r\nAdded the Malay language\r\n<h3>Bugs</h3>\r\nBrowser language redirect (some IE versions)\r\nCustom flag icons do not display on post table columns (posts screen)\r\nSlug translation in LS not working when WPML default language is different than ST original language\r\nLanguage order not applied before first drag\r\nChanging the slug of a taxonomy breaks things\r\nWrong url for custom posts with translated slug.\r\nWPML making Bbpress menu disappear\r\nNotifications not being sent to translators when jobs were cancelled\r\n<h3>Misc</h3>\r\nChanged references to deprecated jQuery function live() -&gt; WPML minimum required WordPress version is now 3.3\r\nWPML Core ‚Äì 2.9\r\nWPML String Translation ‚Äì 1.8\r\nWPML Translation Management ‚Äì 1.7\r\nWPML Media ‚Äì 1.5<h4>2.8.2</h4>Compatible with WordPress 3.6.<h4>2.8.1</h4>Renamed the mobile detection function name to avoid conflicts with other plugins.<h4>2.8</h4>1. Support Different Domains for Languages in WordPress Multisite\r\n2. Mobile-Friendly Language Switcher\r\n3. Allow logging in from on different domains\r\n4. Drag-and-Drop Ordering for Languages<h4>2.7.1</h4>Fixes a few PHP warnings that came up with 2.7 release.<h4>2.7</h4>Improves menu sync functionality and adds a significant performance boost together with the updated String Translation.<h4>2.6.4.1</h4>Added support for Disqus comments, some more fixes of WordPress 3.5 glitches and several small bugs.<h4>2.6.3</h4>Bugfix version that resolves a number of issues related with WordPress 3.5 and some themes and other plugins.<h4>2.6.2</h4><ul>\r\n	<li>Complete support for WordPress 3.5</li>\r\n	<li>Added support for slug translation for custom post types (experimental)</li>\r\n	<li>Fixed a great number of issues with WooCommerce Multilingual</li>\r\n	<li>Moved WPML admin language switcher to WordPress bar</li>\r\n	<li>And a number of bug fixes and overall improvements</li>\r\n</ul><h4>2.6.1</h4>Stability and performance updates. Main bugs fixed include translation for custom fields with serialized arrays and menu synchronization.<h4>2.6.0</h4><ul>\r\n	<li>Added automatic downloading for WordPress translation core</li>\r\n	<li>Improved support for W3TC</li>\r\n	<li>Added fixes for WooCommerce</li>\r\n	<li>Separated the install process to the new Installer plugin</li>\r\n	<li>A bunch of bug fixes and performance improvements</li>\r\n</ul><h4>2.5.2</h4>Fixes several bugs for WordPress multiuser and ICanLocalize interface in WordPress 3.4.<h4>2.5.1</h4>Added support for Google language reference and to convert non ASCII chars in URLs.\r\n\r\nAlso, a good number of fixes and improvements all around.<h4>2.4.3</h4>Stability release with a host of fixes and improvements to existing features.<h4>2.4.2</h4>Adds content duplication logic, which allows displaying untranslated content in different languages.<h4>2.4.1</h4>Allows duplicate post names in different languages.<h4>2.4.0</h4>Added:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Menu Synchronization</strong>¬†- no more need to manually build menus in different languages, WPML can build them for you</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Filter by Parent in the Translation Dashboard</strong>¬†- easily select groups of child pages, or posts by category for translations</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Language Switcher in Menu</strong>¬†- add WPML''s language switcher to WordPress menus</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Author Names Translation Optional</strong>¬†- choose which profiles to translate via the String Translation screen</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Translation for the ‚ÄòUncategorized‚Äô Category</strong>¬†- the default category can have a meaningful name in different languages</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Full Support for Types and Views</strong>¬†- WPML and our new custom data plugin work perfectly together</li>\r\n</ul><h4>2.3.4</h4>Includes complete compatibility with WP E-Commerce (requires the free glue plugin <em>WP E-Commerce Multilingual</em>).<h4>2.3.3</h4>Bugfix release, handling all sorts of issues related with categories, tags and taxonomy.\r\n\r\nAlso, fully tested with WordPress 3.2.<h4>2.3.2</h4>This release improves usability and fixes some potentially confusing parts of WPML.\r\n<h3>What''s new</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Real-time Custom Fields Sync</li>\r\n	<li>Real-time Category and Taxonomy Update</li>\r\n	<li>Translation for Author Fields</li>\r\n	<li>Smarter Admin Language Switcher</li>\r\n	<li>Simplified Theme Localization Options</li>\r\n	<li>Full Support for All GetText Calls</li>\r\n	<li>Synchronization for Publish Date</li>\r\n	<li>Easy to Resign Translators</li>\r\n</ul><h4>2.3.0</h4>Major release with major new functionality:\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Admin bar content-language switcher</li>\r\n<li>Auto-register strings for translation</li>\r\n<li>Sending Strings for translation by your assigned translators</li>\r\n<li>Multilingual-Text Widget</li>\r\n<li>Improvements and fixes to the Translation Editor</li>\r\n<li>Tested with WordPress 3.2</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>2.2.2.1</h4>Fixed a few bugs that were recently introduced:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fatal error for WordPress 3.0 in Multisite mode</li>\r\n<li>Locale value set incorrectly, in conjunction with plugins that load prematurely</li>\r\n<li>WordPress core always trying to upgrade to the default language</li>\r\n<li>Author page URLs incorrect</li>\r\n<li>Pages that begin with language names fail</li>\r\n<li>Negative category names (exclude) not working on translated pages</li>\r\n<li>Endless loop related with categories</li>\r\n<li>PHP notices in some situations</li>\r\n</ul><h4>2.2.2</h4><ul><li>Serious bug fixed, which may lead to loss of language information</li>\r\n<li>Added support for network activation</li>\r\n<li>Improved compatibility with complex themes</li>\r\n<li>Performance improvements and memory reduction in the Admin pages</li>\r\n</ul>";s:7:"version";s:7:"3.1.9.7";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-05-06 08:19:50";s:3:"url";s:47:"https://wpml.org/?download=6088&version=3.1.9.7";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:26:"sitepress-multilingual-cms";}i:1;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:23:"WPML String Translation";s:4:"slug";s:23:"wpml-string-translation";s:11:"description";s:754:"<strong>Allows translating texts in the theme, in other plugins and in the WordPress Admin.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: red;">This is an add-on plugin. It requires the base <em>"WPML Multilingual CMS"</em> to run.</span>\r\n\r\nThe String Translation package includes support for static and dynamic texts.\r\n\r\nStatic texts are hard-coded into the PHP source. Normally, they are translated using .mo files, but with the String Translation package, they can be translated right from within the WordPress Admin.\r\n\r\nDynamic texts is everything that is user-editable. The site''s tagline is an example. Other dynamic texts are often found in the theme settings (like site footer) and in plugins. SEO plugins include many dynamic texts, for titles and meta-data.";s:9:"changelog";s:2996:"<h4>2.1.4</h4>Security tightening.<h4>2.1.3</h4>Fixed a bug related to translating custom post types.<h4>2.1.2</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.9.4 on WordPress 4.2.<h4>2.1.1</h4>Additional fixes to URLs with non-English characters.<h4>2.1</h4>Security update<h4>2.0.14</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.4.<h4>2.0.13</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.3<h4>2.0.12</h4>Updated to fix string registration filter for theme developers.<h4>2.0.11</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.2.<h4>2.0.10</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.<h4>2.0.9.1</h4>Fixed a problem with XML config files, causing PHP errors and untranslated strings.<h4>2.0.9</h4>The fixed dependency bug in 2.0.8 didn''t cover the case of String Translation being activate by users before the WPML core plugin. This was still causing an issue, making the plugin not visible in the menu (and actually not enabled). This should be now fixed.<h4>2.0.8</h4>Fixed dependency issue with WPML core when not active, or during upgrades<h4>2.0.7</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.7.<h4>2.0.6</h4>Update for WPML 3.1.6 with bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>2.0.5</h4>Updates for WordPress 3.9 and PHP 5.5.<h4>2.0.4</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.4.<h4>2.0.1</h4>Small bugfix version for WPML 3.0.1<h4>2.0</h4>WordPress with WPML 3.0.<h4>1.9</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.3.<h4>1.8.2</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.2.<h4>1.8.1</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.1.<h4>1.8</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.<h4>1.7.1</h4>Works with WPML 2.8.2 and WordPress up to 3.6.<h4>1.7</h4>Works with WPML 2.8.<h4>1.6.1</h4>Fixes a bug with translations not showing in version 1.6.<h4>1.6</h4>Up to x2 improvement in site performance.<h4>1.5.4</h4>Bugfix update.<h4>1.5.3</h4>Fixes a number of issues related to WordPress 3.5.<h4>1.5.2</h4>Added support for localizing CPT slugs.<h4>1.5.1</h4>Bugfix release.<h4>1.5.0</h4>Performance improvements and bug fixes.<h4>1.4.0</h4>Major improvements to caching for better performance in public pages and admin pages.<h4>1.3.0</h4>Stability release.<h4>1.2.9</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.2 and includes a number of bug fixes.<h4>1.2.8</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.1.<h4>1.2.7</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.0 and includes a number of new features and improvements.<h4>1.2.6</h4>Includes several bug fixes and translations to new languages.<h4>1.2.5</h4>Fixes issues related with taxonomy. Works with WPML 2.3.3.<h4>1.2.4</h4>Improves usability and fixes some small bugs.<h4>1.2.3</h4>New features:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Added an option to auto-register strings</li>\r\n<li>Admins can send strings to translation using the Translation Management module</li>\r\n</ul><h4>1.2.2.1</h4>Fixes a few errors that were introduced in recent versions.<h4>1.2.2</h4>General performance improvements and bug fixes.<h4>1.2.1</h4>Bugfix release. Brings back the Admin Strings selection with fully working functionality.<h4>1.2.0</h4>Switches direction when editing Right-to-Left strings.<h4>1.1.1</h4>Full support for WordPress 3.1.<h4>1.1.0</h4>Fixes a number of bugs related with custom types.<h4>1.0.0</h4>First release of the commercial version.";s:7:"version";s:5:"2.1.4";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-05-21 13:38:43";s:3:"url";s:45:"https://wpml.org/?download=6092&version=2.1.4";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:23:"wpml-string-translation";}i:2;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:27:"WPML Translation Management";s:4:"slug";s:27:"wpml-translation-management";s:11:"description";s:1260:"<strong>The Translation Management package helps run translations for large WordPress sites.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: red;">This is an add-on plugin. It requires the base <em>"WPML Multilingual CMS"</em> to run.</span>\r\n\r\n<dl><dt>Translator Role</dt><dd>Site admins can turn ordinary WordPress users into translators. Translators can only edit specific content that was assigned to them for translation.</dd><dt>Centralized translation control</dt><dd>Admins get a complete overview of what''s already translated and what needs translation or update. They can send content to translation to specific translators and track progress.</dd><dt>Translation queues</dt><dd>Each translator has a queue of pending jobs. Translators don''t need to look for what to do, it just waits for them.</dd><dt>Side-by-Side translation editor</dt><dd>When translating, you see both the original and translation and what changed. You can conveniently move from one field to the other, and switch between Visual and HTML views.</dd><dt>Automatic link translation</dt><dd>Translators don''t need to worry about interlinked content. WPML will automatically update links to point to other translated content. Translators only need to translate the text and nothing else.</dd></dl>";s:9:"changelog";s:2468:"<h4>1.9.11</h4>Additional fixes to URLs with non-English characters<h4>1.9.10</h4>Security update<h4>1.9.9</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.4<h4>1.9.8</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.3.<h4>1.9.7</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.<h4>1.9.6</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.7.<h4>1.9.5</h4>Update for WPML 3.1.6 with bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>1.9.4</h4>Updates for WordPress 3.9 and PHP 5.5.<h4>1.9.3</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.4.<h4>1.9.1</h4>Small bugfix version for WPML 3.0.1<h4>1.9</h4>Works with WPML 3.0.<h4>1.8</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.3.<h4>1.7.2</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.2.<h4>1.7.1</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.1.<h4>1.7</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.<h4>1.6.1</h4>Works with WPML 2.8.2 and WordPress 3.6.<h4>1.6</h4>Works with WPML 2.8<h4>1.5</h4>New option for selecting documents.<h4>1.4.4</h4>Added checks to prevent errors with documents that have illegal character names.<h4>1.4.3</h4>Fixes a number of issues related with WordPress 3.5.<h4>1.4.2</h4>Added a new display filter for content that needs updating (but it not new)<h4>1.4.1</h4>Bugfix release.<h4>1.4.0</h4>Changed cost estimate for ICanLocalize translation and fixed a number of warnings and notices.<h4>1.3.1</h4>Fixes some bugs with ICanLocalize interface. Works with WPML 2.5.2.<h4>1.3.0</h4>Improvements for translation of custom fields, with complete support for repeating fields.<h4>1.2.9</h4>Stability release.<h4>1.2.8</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.2 and includes the content duplication logic.<h4>1.2.7</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.1.<h4>1.2.6</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.0 and includes a number of new features and improvements. The filter section in the Translation Dashboard has been enhanced for better usability and allows selecting items by parent.<h4>1.2.5</h4>Updated to support new functionality for WP E-Commerce and several bug fixes.<h4>1.2.4</h4>Improves usability and fixes several small bugs.<h4>1.2.3</h4>Allows translating strings using the assigned translators.<h4>1.2.2</h4>Added automatic link updates for translated pages.<h4>1.2.1</h4>Bugfix release.<h4>1.2.0</h4><ul>\r\n<li>Added Right-to-Left support.</li>\r\n<li>Displays the existing translation when sending documents for update.</li>\r\n<li>Shows the difference between previous originals to current originals when updating translations.</li>\r\n</ul><h4>1.1.1</h4>Added full support for WordPress 3.1.<h4>1.1.0</h4>Fixed a bug:\r\n\r\n"Jobs can remain in stuck state if sending to incorrect translators"<h4>1.0.0</h4>First release of the commercial version.";s:7:"version";s:6:"1.9.11";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-03-12 16:09:05";s:3:"url";s:46:"https://wpml.org/?download=6094&version=1.9.11";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:27:"wpml-translation-management";}i:3;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:17:"WPML Sticky Links";s:4:"slug";s:17:"wpml-sticky-links";s:11:"description";s:894:"<strong>Turns all internal links into unbreakable, by following the document that''s being linked to.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: red;">This is an add-on plugin. It requires the base <em>"WPML Multilingual CMS"</em> to run.</span>\r\n\r\nPages, posts, categories, tags and custom types all have default URLs. These URLs point to the object ID. No matter what changes the pages undergo, the IDs always remain the same, identifying them in the CMS.\r\n\r\nThis plugin converts all links in the DB to the default URLs. Then, just as the pages are displayed, it replaces the links back to the permalinks.\r\n\r\nWhen you view the DB, you''ll see ''ugly'' looking links. However, when visitors view your site, they would always see the up-to-date links.\r\n\r\nYou can change slugs, hierarchy and permalink structure and all links always remain valid.\r\n\r\nSee the <a href="/?page_id=594">Sticky Links user guide</a>.";s:9:"changelog";s:1318:"<h4>1.3.9</h4>Additional fixes to URLs with non-English characters<h4>1.3.8</h4>Security update<h4>1.3.7</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.4<h4>1.3.6</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.<h4>1.3.5</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.7.<h4>1.3.4</h4>Update for WPML 3.1.6 with bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>1.3.3</h4>Updates for WordPress 3.9 and PHP 5.5.<h4>1.3.2</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.4.<h4>1.3</h4>Updated translations.<h4>1.2.1</h4>Bugfix release<h4>1.2.0</h4>Fixed a number of bugs related to reverting Sticky Links in different URL formats. Also improved Sticky Link detection in content.<h4>1.1.8</h4>Stability release<h4>1.1.7</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.0 and includes a number of new features and improvements.<h4>1.1.6</h4>Includes several bug fixes and translations to new languages.<h4>1.1.5</h4>Fixes issues related with taxonomy translation. Works with WPML 2.3.3.<h4>1.1.4</h4>Fixes a number of issues and improves Sticky Links for taxonomies. Works with WPML 2.3.1.<h4>1.1.3</h4>Improved performance and small bug fixes.<h4>1.1.2</h4>Improved support for multiple pages with the same name.<h4>1.1.1</h4>Bugfix release.<h4>1.1.0</h4>Fixed Sticky Links functionality for links that include classes and other attributes.<h4>1.0.1</h4>Added full support for WordPress 3.1.<h4>1.0.0</h4>First release of the commercial version.";s:7:"version";s:5:"1.3.9";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-03-12 16:09:43";s:3:"url";s:45:"https://wpml.org/?download=6090&version=1.3.9";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:17:"wpml-sticky-links";}i:4;a:11:{s:4:"name";s:26:"WPML Translation Analytics";s:4:"slug";s:26:"wpml-translation-analytics";s:11:"description";s:588:"<p><strong>Helps site admins manage and track the status of translation work.</strong></p>\r\n<p>When you''re working with a team of translators, often located in different parts of the world and working different hours, staying on top of translation progress can be complicated.</p>\r\n<p>This plugin will let you manage your site''s translation easily and efficiently. You''ll immediately see the current status of translation, progress over time, and how you''re doing compared to project deadlines.</p>\r\n<p>This plugin requires the base WPML and Translation Management, in order to run.</p>\r\n";s:9:"changelog";s:318:"<h4>1.0.7</h4>Security update<h4>1.0.6</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.7<h4>1.0.5</h4>Update for WPML 3.1.6 with bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>1.0.4</h4>Updates for WordPress 3.9 and PHP 5.5.<h4>1.0.3</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.4.<h4>1.0.1</h4>Complete translation to several languages.<h4>1.0.0</h4>Initial release.";s:7:"version";s:5:"1.0.7";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-03-10 10:13:31";s:3:"url";s:46:"https://wpml.org/?download=78197&version=1.0.7";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:26:"wpml-translation-analytics";s:15:"version-for-icl";s:5:"1.0.6";s:11:"url-for-icl";s:46:"https://wpml.org/?download=78197&version=1.0.6";}i:5;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:12:"WPML CMS Nav";s:4:"slug";s:12:"wpml-cms-nav";s:11:"description";s:589:"<strong>Creates navigation elements, which you can use with any theme.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: red;">This is an add-on plugin. It requires the base <em>"WPML Multilingual CMS"</em> to run.</span>\r\n\r\n<dl><dt>Breadcrumb trail</dt><dd>Shows a trail back to the home page.</dd><dt>Sidebar navigation</dt><dd>A widget that you can add to the sidebar. It shows the current page next to neighboring pages.</dd><dt>Drop-down menu</dt><dd>Shows the site''s top-level pages and their child pages. The drop-down menu supports item-hooks, which allow customizing the content of cells.</dd></dl>";s:9:"changelog";s:1050:"<h4>1.4.7</h4>Security update<h4>1.4.6</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.4.<h4>1.4.5</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.7.<h4>1.4.4</h4>Update for WPML 3.1.6 with bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>1.4.3</h4>Updates for WordPress 3.9 and PHP 5.5.<h4>1.4.2</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.4.<h4>1.4</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.3.<h4>1.3</h4>Translations update.<h4>1.2.7</h4>Fixed several minor security notices.<h4>1.2.6</h4>Stability release<h4>1.2.5</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.0 and includes a number of new features and improvements.<h4>1.2.4</h4>Includes small bug fixes and new translation files.<h4>1.2.3</h4>Mainly bug fixes and support for new functionality in WPML 2.3.0.<h4>1.2.2</h4>Fixed bugs related with navigation caching, to improve performance and reduce DB size.<h4>1.2.1</h4>Bugfix release.<h4>1.2.0</h4>Added full support for Custom Post Archives in the breadcrumbs trail.<h4>1.1.1</h4>Added full support for WordPress 3.1.<h4>1.1.0</h4>Fixes a number of bugs, related with navigation for custom types.<h4>1.0.0</h4>First release of the commercial version.";s:7:"version";s:5:"1.4.7";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-03-10 10:13:50";s:3:"url";s:45:"https://wpml.org/?download=6096&version=1.4.7";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:12:"wpml-cms-nav";}i:6;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:10:"WPML Media";s:4:"slug";s:10:"wpml-media";s:11:"description";s:603:"Manages translations for WordPress Media. This plugin will allow to use the same uploaded media (images, audio, movies, etc.) in different translations, without having to re-upload duplicate content.\r\n\r\nWhen you insert media to posts and pages, Media Translation will offer to auto-duplicate it to translations. Then, when you use the WordPress <em>gallery</em> shorttag, the same images will appear in all translations.\r\n\r\nMedia Translation also auto-sets featured images for translation.\r\n\r\nIt works in different translation modes. You can create translations manually or using the Translation Editor.";s:9:"changelog";s:1482:"<h4>2.1.9</h4>Security update<h4>2.1.8</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.4.<h4>2.1.7</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.<h4>2.1.6</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.7.<h4>2.1.5</h4>Update for WPML 3.1.6 with bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>2.1.4</h4>Updates for WordPress 3.9 and PHP 5.5.<h4>2.1.3</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.4.<h4>2.1.1</h4>Small bugfix version for WPML 3.0.1<h4>2.1</h4>Improvements for WooCommerce Multilingual 3.0.<h4>2.0.2</h4>Uses the same language mapping as all other WPML components use. Fully supports WooCommerce.<h4>1.6</h4>New GUI that makes the functionality of the Media Translation a lot clearer.\r\nFixed a number of issues with media items not getting languages and disappearing from the WordPress admin.\r\nImproved synchronization for featured images in different languages.<h4>1.5</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.<h4>1.4</h4>Bug fixes.<h4>1.3</h4>Stability improvements.<h4>1.2.3</h4>Fixed a bug with WordPress prepare statement for 3.5.<h4>1.2.2</h4>Fixes a number of issues with WordPress 3.5.<h4>1.2.1</h4>Bugfix release.<h4>1.2.0</h4>Major performance improvements.<h4>1.1.0</h4>Fixes a bug that caused attachments uploaded via the Media management screen to not have language information.<h4>1.0.1</h4>Small bug fixes and added translations.<h4>1.0.0</h4>First release. Look for the new controls in the language boxes when editing posts. There''s also a new menu, <em>WPML-&gt;Media translation</em>, that allows to auto-generate duplicate Attachments for existing content.";s:7:"version";s:5:"2.1.9";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-03-10 10:14:10";s:3:"url";s:45:"https://wpml.org/?download=7474&version=2.1.9";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:10:"wpml-media";}i:7;a:11:{s:4:"name";s:10:"WPML XLIFF";s:4:"slug";s:10:"wpml-xliff";s:11:"description";s:692:"<strong>The XLIFF package allows exporting translation jobs to desktop translation software.</strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: red;">This is an add-on plugin. It requires the base <em>"WPML Multilingual CMS"</em> to run.</span>\r\n\r\nThis package creates XLIFF files and includes them in the translation job notification emails. Translators will be able to use their favorite CAT tools to translate offline and return the translations to WPML.\r\n\r\nIn order to use it, you must install WPML Translation Management. The XLIFF interface is added to the translation jobs list and notification emails.\r\n\r\nYou can read about how it works in the <a href="/?page_id=8012">XLIFF interface documentation</a>.";s:9:"changelog";s:471:"<h4>0.9.8</h4>Security update<h4>0.9.7</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.<h4>0.9.6</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.7.<h4>0.9.5</h4>Update for WPML 3.1.6 with bug fixes and performance improvements. Allows to choose the XLIFF version when generating files.<h4>0.9.4</h4>Updates for WordPress 3.9 and PHP 5.5.<h4>0.9.3</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.4.<h4>0.9.1</h4>Stability release<h4>0.9.0</h4>First release. This release is tested with a number of CAT tools including Trados, MemQ and others.";s:7:"version";s:5:"0.9.8";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-03-10 10:14:34";s:3:"url";s:45:"https://wpml.org/?download=8066&version=0.9.8";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:10:"wpml-xliff";s:15:"version-for-icl";s:5:"0.9.7";s:11:"url-for-icl";s:45:"https://wpml.org/?download=8066&version=0.9.7";}i:8;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:26:"Gravity Forms Multilingual";s:4:"slug";s:25:"gravityforms-multilingual";s:11:"description";s:333:"Allows to use WPML with Gravity Forms, to create multilingual contact forms.\r\n\r\nTo use this plugin, you''ll need WPML''s <strong>String Translation</strong> and <strong>Translation Management</strong> modules. Once installed, go to the <strong>Translation Dashboard</strong>. There, you''ll see the contact forms, ready for translation.";s:9:"changelog";s:455:"<h4>1.2.2</h4>Added support for Gravity Forms 1.9.x.\r\nSecurity fixes.<h4>1.2.1</h4>Added support for more GravityForms fields for features.<h4>1.2</h4>Added support for more GravityForms features.<h4>1.1</h4>Added support for new Gravity Forms texts and validation messages.<h4>0.9.3</h4>Fixed the language of the ''thank you'' page.<h4>0.9.2</h4>Fixes a number of issues with special characters in form fields.<h4>0.9.1</h4>Works with WPML 2.4.1 and above.";s:7:"version";s:5:"1.2.2";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-03-12 16:21:47";s:3:"url";s:45:"https://wpml.org/?download=8882&version=1.2.2";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:25:"gravityforms-multilingual";}}}}}i:451016;a:7:{s:2:"id";s:17:"multilingual-blog";s:4:"name";s:17:"Multilingual Blog";s:11:"description";s:52:"The basic WPML version, good for multilingual blogs.";s:9:"image_url";s:61:"https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/wpml-logo1-01.png";s:5:"order";i:0;s:6:"parent";i:0;s:8:"products";a:1:{s:17:"multilingual-blog";a:10:{s:4:"name";s:17:"Multilingual Blog";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:5:"price";s:2:"29";s:17:"subscription_type";i:6718;s:22:"subscription_type_text";s:17:"Multilingual Blog";s:17:"subscription_info";s:19:"Yearly subscription";s:3:"url";s:50:"https://wpml.org/?add-to-cart=162034&amp;buy_now=1";s:8:"renewals";a:1:{s:25:"multilingual-blog-renewal";a:5:{s:4:"name";s:25:"Multilingual Blog renewal";s:11:"call2action";s:0:"";s:11:"description";s:97:"Extend your Multilingual Blog account by another year, providing continuous support and upgrades.";s:5:"price";s:2:"15";s:3:"url";s:50:"https://wpml.org/?add-to-cart=162036&amp;buy_now=1";}}s:8:"upgrades";a:2:{s:43:"multilingual-cms-for-life-upgrade-from-blog";a:7:{s:4:"name";s:43:"Multilingual CMS for life upgrade from Blog";s:11:"call2action";s:0:"";s:11:"description";s:156:"Upgrade from the basic Multilingual Blog to the full Multilingual CMS Lifetime package to receive access to all of WPML''s modules and functionality forever.";s:5:"price";s:3:"166";s:17:"subscription_type";i:6721;s:3:"url";s:50:"https://wpml.org/?add-to-cart=162040&amp;buy_now=1";s:17:"including_expired";i:1;}s:34:"multilingual-cms-upgrade-from-blog";a:7:{s:4:"name";s:34:"Multilingual CMS upgrade from Blog";s:11:"call2action";s:0:"";s:11:"description";s:139:"Upgrade from the basic Multilingual Blog to the full Multilingual CMS package to receive access to all of WPML''s modules and functionality.";s:5:"price";s:2:"50";s:17:"subscription_type";i:6719;s:3:"url";s:50:"https://wpml.org/?add-to-cart=162038&amp;buy_now=1";s:17:"including_expired";i:1;}}s:9:"downloads";a:2:{i:0;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:21:"WPML Multilingual CMS";s:4:"slug";s:26:"sitepress-multilingual-cms";s:11:"description";s:782:"WPML combines multilingual content authoring with powerful translation management. It powers corporate sites and is simple enough for bloggers.\r\n\r\n<dl><dt>Turns WordPress multilingual</dt><dd>Every element in WordPress becomes multilingual. This include pages, posts, tags, categories, custom types and even comments.</dd><dt>Virtual language directories and languages in different domains</dt><dd>You can display translations in URLs such as <em>example.com/es/</em>, <em>example.com/fr/</em> or in completely different domains, or sub-domains, per language.</dd><dt>Convenient translation controls</dt><dd>When you view the lists of pages and posts, you''ll see what''s already translated and what not. You can add translations from the list-view or while editing content.</dd></dl>";s:9:"changelog";s:8726:"<h4>3.1.9.7</h4>Fixed a problem with menu translation<h4>3.1.9.6</h4>* Security fixes<h4>3.1.9.5</h4>* "Illegal mix of collation" error\r\n* Categories by languages are not displayed<h4>3.1.9.4</h4>Added support for WordPress 4.2.<h4>3.1.9.3</h4>Additional fixes to URLs with non-English characters.<h4>3.1.9.2</h4>Fixed issue with saving posts that have slugs in different languages.<h4>3.1.9.1</h4>Fixed URL resolution for non-English URLs.<h4>3.1.9</h4>Security update<h4>3.1.8.6</h4>Small improvement to mechanism for remote config files.<h4>3.1.8.5</h4>Small improvement to Installer, which will help get WPML updates.<h4>3.1.8.4</h4>Fixed several incompatibilities with WooCommerce, menu translation and taxonomy translation.<h4>3.1.8.3</h4>Stability update - fixes issues with the taxonomy translation admin screen in WPML and WooCommerce multilingual.<h4>3.1.8.2</h4>Updated to fix issue with taxonomy translation page and duplicate media items.<h4>3.1.8.1</h4>Quick fix for WooCommerce updates.<h4>3.1.8</h4>Major updates to taxonomy translation and general stability improvements.<h4>3.1.7.2</h4>* Removed mistakenly added anonymous function, causing issues with versions of PHP <5.3\r\n* Fixed for wrong usage of static method\r\n<h4>3.1.7.1</h4>Fixed glitch with translation management<h4>3.1.7</h4>Moved Installer back to WPML and a number of other improvements.<h4>3.1.6</h4>Bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>3.1.5</h4>Full compatibility for WordPress 3.9 and updates for PHP 5.5.<h4>3.1.4</h4>Major performance and stability updates.<h4>3.0.2-a</h4>Fixes a bug which caused translations to be disconnected in some situations.<h4>3.0.1</h4>Tiny bugfix version for "cannot delete" message and other small glitches<h4>3.0</h4>New GUI, better menu sync and big improvements for multilingual e-commerce.<h4>2.9.3</h4>A great number of improvements and fixes and WooCommerce Multilingual.<h4>2.9.2</h4>Removes deprecation warnings on WordPress 3.6.\r\nImproves performance when scanning many new strings.<h4>2.9.1</h4>This is a bugfix release, addressing some issues that came up in WPML 2.9:\r\n\r\n* Slug translation issues\r\n* Content appearing twice with some themes\r\n* Content disappeared from the WordPress admin\r\n* WPML didn‚Äôt mark duplicate content as duplicate\r\n<h4>2.9</h4><h3>Features</h3>\r\nTitle tags added to navigation\r\nrel=canonical now optional configurable under WPML -&gt; Languages ‚Üí SEO Options\r\nAllow to select all languages when sending documents to translation from the Translation Dashboard\r\nImproved Import/export .po from String Translation screen\r\nFlag only language switcher. Including horizontal layout.\r\nPreserve url parameters in the language switcher\r\nUse directory for default language\r\nDuplicate all custom fields and taxonomy when duplicating the post\r\nNew function in the Troubleshooting section to set update translation tables after changing the slug for custom posts or custom taxonomies that had translated elements.\r\nAllow re-assigning translation jobs\r\nSupport wildcards in wpml-config.xml for entries in the options table\r\nAdded the Malay language\r\n<h3>Bugs</h3>\r\nBrowser language redirect (some IE versions)\r\nCustom flag icons do not display on post table columns (posts screen)\r\nSlug translation in LS not working when WPML default language is different than ST original language\r\nLanguage order not applied before first drag\r\nChanging the slug of a taxonomy breaks things\r\nWrong url for custom posts with translated slug.\r\nWPML making Bbpress menu disappear\r\nNotifications not being sent to translators when jobs were cancelled\r\n<h3>Misc</h3>\r\nChanged references to deprecated jQuery function live() -&gt; WPML minimum required WordPress version is now 3.3\r\nWPML Core ‚Äì 2.9\r\nWPML String Translation ‚Äì 1.8\r\nWPML Translation Management ‚Äì 1.7\r\nWPML Media ‚Äì 1.5<h4>2.8.2</h4>Compatible with WordPress 3.6.<h4>2.8.1</h4>Renamed the mobile detection function name to avoid conflicts with other plugins.<h4>2.8</h4>1. Support Different Domains for Languages in WordPress Multisite\r\n2. Mobile-Friendly Language Switcher\r\n3. Allow logging in from on different domains\r\n4. Drag-and-Drop Ordering for Languages<h4>2.7.1</h4>Fixes a few PHP warnings that came up with 2.7 release.<h4>2.7</h4>Improves menu sync functionality and adds a significant performance boost together with the updated String Translation.<h4>2.6.4.1</h4>Added support for Disqus comments, some more fixes of WordPress 3.5 glitches and several small bugs.<h4>2.6.3</h4>Bugfix version that resolves a number of issues related with WordPress 3.5 and some themes and other plugins.<h4>2.6.2</h4><ul>\r\n	<li>Complete support for WordPress 3.5</li>\r\n	<li>Added support for slug translation for custom post types (experimental)</li>\r\n	<li>Fixed a great number of issues with WooCommerce Multilingual</li>\r\n	<li>Moved WPML admin language switcher to WordPress bar</li>\r\n	<li>And a number of bug fixes and overall improvements</li>\r\n</ul><h4>2.6.1</h4>Stability and performance updates. Main bugs fixed include translation for custom fields with serialized arrays and menu synchronization.<h4>2.6.0</h4><ul>\r\n	<li>Added automatic downloading for WordPress translation core</li>\r\n	<li>Improved support for W3TC</li>\r\n	<li>Added fixes for WooCommerce</li>\r\n	<li>Separated the install process to the new Installer plugin</li>\r\n	<li>A bunch of bug fixes and performance improvements</li>\r\n</ul><h4>2.5.2</h4>Fixes several bugs for WordPress multiuser and ICanLocalize interface in WordPress 3.4.<h4>2.5.1</h4>Added support for Google language reference and to convert non ASCII chars in URLs.\r\n\r\nAlso, a good number of fixes and improvements all around.<h4>2.4.3</h4>Stability release with a host of fixes and improvements to existing features.<h4>2.4.2</h4>Adds content duplication logic, which allows displaying untranslated content in different languages.<h4>2.4.1</h4>Allows duplicate post names in different languages.<h4>2.4.0</h4>Added:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Menu Synchronization</strong>¬†- no more need to manually build menus in different languages, WPML can build them for you</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Filter by Parent in the Translation Dashboard</strong>¬†- easily select groups of child pages, or posts by category for translations</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Language Switcher in Menu</strong>¬†- add WPML''s language switcher to WordPress menus</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Author Names Translation Optional</strong>¬†- choose which profiles to translate via the String Translation screen</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Translation for the ‚ÄòUncategorized‚Äô Category</strong>¬†- the default category can have a meaningful name in different languages</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Full Support for Types and Views</strong>¬†- WPML and our new custom data plugin work perfectly together</li>\r\n</ul><h4>2.3.4</h4>Includes complete compatibility with WP E-Commerce (requires the free glue plugin <em>WP E-Commerce Multilingual</em>).<h4>2.3.3</h4>Bugfix release, handling all sorts of issues related with categories, tags and taxonomy.\r\n\r\nAlso, fully tested with WordPress 3.2.<h4>2.3.2</h4>This release improves usability and fixes some potentially confusing parts of WPML.\r\n<h3>What''s new</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Real-time Custom Fields Sync</li>\r\n	<li>Real-time Category and Taxonomy Update</li>\r\n	<li>Translation for Author Fields</li>\r\n	<li>Smarter Admin Language Switcher</li>\r\n	<li>Simplified Theme Localization Options</li>\r\n	<li>Full Support for All GetText Calls</li>\r\n	<li>Synchronization for Publish Date</li>\r\n	<li>Easy to Resign Translators</li>\r\n</ul><h4>2.3.0</h4>Major release with major new functionality:\r\n\r\n<ul><li>Admin bar content-language switcher</li>\r\n<li>Auto-register strings for translation</li>\r\n<li>Sending Strings for translation by your assigned translators</li>\r\n<li>Multilingual-Text Widget</li>\r\n<li>Improvements and fixes to the Translation Editor</li>\r\n<li>Tested with WordPress 3.2</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>2.2.2.1</h4>Fixed a few bugs that were recently introduced:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fatal error for WordPress 3.0 in Multisite mode</li>\r\n<li>Locale value set incorrectly, in conjunction with plugins that load prematurely</li>\r\n<li>WordPress core always trying to upgrade to the default language</li>\r\n<li>Author page URLs incorrect</li>\r\n<li>Pages that begin with language names fail</li>\r\n<li>Negative category names (exclude) not working on translated pages</li>\r\n<li>Endless loop related with categories</li>\r\n<li>PHP notices in some situations</li>\r\n</ul><h4>2.2.2</h4><ul><li>Serious bug fixed, which may lead to loss of language information</li>\r\n<li>Added support for network activation</li>\r\n<li>Improved compatibility with complex themes</li>\r\n<li>Performance improvements and memory reduction in the Admin pages</li>\r\n</ul>";s:7:"version";s:7:"3.1.9.7";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-05-06 08:19:50";s:3:"url";s:47:"https://wpml.org/?download=6088&version=3.1.9.7";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:26:"sitepress-multilingual-cms";}i:1;a:9:{s:4:"name";s:10:"WPML Media";s:4:"slug";s:10:"wpml-media";s:11:"description";s:603:"Manages translations for WordPress Media. This plugin will allow to use the same uploaded media (images, audio, movies, etc.) in different translations, without having to re-upload duplicate content.\r\n\r\nWhen you insert media to posts and pages, Media Translation will offer to auto-duplicate it to translations. Then, when you use the WordPress <em>gallery</em> shorttag, the same images will appear in all translations.\r\n\r\nMedia Translation also auto-sets featured images for translation.\r\n\r\nIt works in different translation modes. You can create translations manually or using the Translation Editor.";s:9:"changelog";s:1482:"<h4>2.1.9</h4>Security update<h4>2.1.8</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.4.<h4>2.1.7</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.8.<h4>2.1.6</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.7.<h4>2.1.5</h4>Update for WPML 3.1.6 with bug fixes and performance improvements.<h4>2.1.4</h4>Updates for WordPress 3.9 and PHP 5.5.<h4>2.1.3</h4>Works with WPML 3.1.4.<h4>2.1.1</h4>Small bugfix version for WPML 3.0.1<h4>2.1</h4>Improvements for WooCommerce Multilingual 3.0.<h4>2.0.2</h4>Uses the same language mapping as all other WPML components use. Fully supports WooCommerce.<h4>1.6</h4>New GUI that makes the functionality of the Media Translation a lot clearer.\r\nFixed a number of issues with media items not getting languages and disappearing from the WordPress admin.\r\nImproved synchronization for featured images in different languages.<h4>1.5</h4>Works with WPML 2.9.<h4>1.4</h4>Bug fixes.<h4>1.3</h4>Stability improvements.<h4>1.2.3</h4>Fixed a bug with WordPress prepare statement for 3.5.<h4>1.2.2</h4>Fixes a number of issues with WordPress 3.5.<h4>1.2.1</h4>Bugfix release.<h4>1.2.0</h4>Major performance improvements.<h4>1.1.0</h4>Fixes a bug that caused attachments uploaded via the Media management screen to not have language information.<h4>1.0.1</h4>Small bug fixes and added translations.<h4>1.0.0</h4>First release. Look for the new controls in the language boxes when editing posts. There''s also a new menu, <em>WPML-&gt;Media translation</em>, that allows to auto-generate duplicate Attachments for existing content.";s:7:"version";s:5:"2.1.9";s:4:"date";s:19:"2015-03-10 10:14:10";s:3:"url";s:45:"https://wpml.org/?download=7474&version=2.1.9";s:13:"free-on-wporg";i:0;s:8:"basename";s:10:"wpml-media";}}}}}}s:9:"downloads";a:2:{s:6:"themes";a:0:{}s:7:"plugins";a:0:{}}s:18:"subscriptions_meta";a:1:{s:10:"expiration";a:1:{i:9651;a:2:{s:12:"days_warning";s:0:"";s:15:"warning_message";s:0:"";}}}s:12:"localization";a:0:{}s:4:"hash";s:32:"6e1fb9f3147e28072970324da299768c";}}}s:24:"last_repositories_update";i:1432623810;s:14:"dismissed_nags";a:1:{s:4:"wpml";i:1;}}', 'yes');
